 has made possible the study of genetic structure of populations through time laboratory work includes morphometric and molecular analyses with the intent to extend the level of investigation down to the population and genetic levels ongoing projects at the macroecological scale include the study of the ecological and evolutionary factors influencing biological diversity through a comparison of temperate terrestrial vertebrate faunas in north and south america publications cap profiles with similar publication topics publication tag cloud publication topics what is this feedback close genetic variation over 10000 years in ctenomys comparative phylochronology provides a temporal perspective on rarity environmental change and demography chan yl hadly ea mol ecol 2011 20 22 4592 605 developmental dynamics of ambystoma tigrinum in a changing landscape mcmenamin sk hadly ea bmc ecol 2010 10 10 dispersal provided resilience to range collapse in a marine mammal insights from the past to inform conservation biology pinsky ml newsome sd dickerson br fang y van tuinen m kennett dj ream rr hadly ea mol ecol 2010 19 12 2418 29 small mammal diversity loss in response to late pleistocene climatic change blois jl mcguire jl hadly ea nature 2010 465 7299 771 4 niche conservatism above the species level hadly ea spaeth pa li c proc natl acad sci us a 2009 106 suppl 2 19707 14 view all 20 you are here home faculty navigation for this section department of biology education & training courses faculty research sites about us contact us search profiles by name help community academic profiles stanford only login update your profile connect with colleagues find a researcher profiles by name profiles by department profiles by program help go stanford only login update your profile connect with colleagues site navigation home faculty education & training biology events giving to biology stanford medicine resources stanford medicine getting care overview find a physician find a clinical car